$interpreted: Clark: Your Majesty, the Queen. You called for me?
Diana: I've been told you wish to travel to the Mechanical Territory. Is this true?
Clark: Yes. But from what I understand, there are currently no boats heading there from the Desert Kingdom.

Diana: Actually, the current situation in the Mechanical Territory isn't looking so good. 
I'm planning on sending some investigators to assist in restoring trade relations.
Clark: So...you'll send a ship?
Diana: As an expression of thanks for the help you provided the Desert Kingdom, I'll arrange for the ship to take you to the Mechanical Territory.
Clark: Really!? Thank you so much!
Diana: However, the season where the Walruses are most ferocious is soon approaching. I can only send a ship with the most skilled of sailors.
Clark: So we're pressed for time...
Clark: But Maria, she...
Diana: Your robot friend still cannot be turned on?
Clark: The damage is pretty severe. It will be difficult to fix given my skill level.
Clark: I remember there's a mechanician in the Desert Bazaar. I planned on taking Maria there to ask him for assistance.
Diana: We still need a month's time to prepare the boat and supplies. I hope you can return within one month, before the ship sets sail.
Clark: One month...
Diana: In order to avoid the ferocious Walruses, the ship must set sail on time.
Diana: If we want to send more ships, I'm afraid we'll need to wait another three to four months.
Clark: I'll set out immediately. I'll be sure to make it back in time.
Clark: Thank you, Your Highness.
Diana: Safe travels.
Clark: Huff...puff...no way. I'm gonna have a heat stroke.
Clark: I've been in the desert for five days already. Should've gotten there by now...
Chu Chu: Chu...chu...
Clark: Don't worry, Chu Chu. I'll fix you once I get all the parts.
Clark: Hills? The hills we're looking for?
Clark: I'm not lost, am I....?
Clark: If only Maria was here...
Clark: Wait a sec, if Maria wasn't broken, I wouldn't have come to this godforsaken place...
Clark: It's already...been...ten days...since we set out.
Clark: If we don't make it in time...
Clark: No, can't let that happen.
Clark: Come on, Maria. Let's go. I'm going to fix you.
Clark: ......
Clark: Ohhh crap...!
Clark: This...is not looking good...
Ned: Hey!
Ned: Get outta the way!
Ned: You alright?
Clark: I'm fine, just in...a little pain...thanks for saving me.
Ned: You're not from around here, huh? This is their feeding ground. Locals don't dare come here.
Clark: I'm looking for a mechanician named Sherlock. I'm lost...
Ned: Sherlock? You're looking for Father?
Clark: You're his son!?
Ned: Actually, I'm married to his daughter.
Clark: I've been searching for days...
Ned: You've been traveling in the completely wrong direction...
Clark: Can you take me to him? It's important.
Ned: No problem. Come with me!
Ned: I'll wrap up your wounds in a bit.
Ned: You're hurt, I'll carry you.
Ned: Didn't think your luggage would be so damn heavy!
Clark: Haha...thank...you...
